
    // FILE IO

File IO in java is used to read from and write tot files.

Java provides classes and methods within Java.io & java.nio packages for file operations, including reading, writing and manipulating file data.

File IO is commonly used for tasks such as storing and retrieving data, reading configurations and logging.


common methods

createNewFile(): creates a new empty file.
mkdir(): creates a new directory
exists(): checks if the file/directory exists.
delete(): Deletes the file or directory.


FileReader & FileWriter

FileReader reads from the file
